  <header>
    <h1>How to Choose the Perfect Luxury Bag</h1>
    <p class="meta">By Luxora Editorial Team | September 2025</p>
  </header>

  <figure>
    <img src="images/hermes-bag.jpg" alt="Hermès Birkin bag on display in luxury boutique">
    <figcaption>The Hermès Birkin: the ultimate symbol of timeless sophistication.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <section>
    <h2>The Allure of Luxury Bags</h2>
    <p>
      A luxury bag is more than an accessory; it is a cultural icon, a piece of art, and often, an investment. For decades, houses like <strong>Hermès, Chanel, and Louis Vuitton</strong> have set the gold standard, producing handbags that not only define fashion but embody legacy. To own a luxury bag is to own a piece of history.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Hermès: The Crown Jewel of Handbags</h2>
    <p>
      When one speaks of luxury handbags, the conversation inevitably leads to Hermès. The <strong>Birkin</strong> and the <strong>Kelly</strong> are not just bags—they are cultural milestones. Entire waiting lists form for the chance to purchase one, with certain exotic leather editions reaching auction prices in the hundreds of thousands.
    </p>
    <p>
      The fanciest Hermès bags are crafted from rare skins such as <em>crocodile, ostrich, and lizard</em>, often finished with 18k gold or even diamond hardware. These creations are not only fashion statements but collectible masterpieces.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How to Choose the Right Bag</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Consider if the bag is for everyday wear or special occasions.</li>
      <li><strong>Material:</strong> Calfskin and togo leather for durability, exotic skins for exclusivity.</li>
      <li><strong>Size:</strong> A 25cm Birkin exudes elegance, while a 35cm fits modern practicality.</li>
      <li><strong>Investment Value:</strong> Certain limited editions appreciate over time, making them as valuable as fine jewelry.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why Luxury Bags Matter</h2>
    <p>
      Beyond fashion, luxury bags are emotional and financial investments. They capture a moment in time, represent milestones, and often become heirlooms. Choosing the right bag means choosing an object that will carry your story for generations.
    </p>
  </section>
</article>